  <static seed="46" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring77.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{36x^{5}-40x^{4}+12x^{3}}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>4x^{3}\mathopen{}\left(9x^{2}-10x+3\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>4x^3</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{36x^{5}-40x^{4}+12x^{3}}={4x^{3}\mathopen{}\left(9x^{2}-10x+3\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
